  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at AIG?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at AIG, or any large organization, can be both exciting and overwhelming. Here are some key things new employees should know to help them navigate their first day and beyond:\n\n1. **Company Culture**: Familiarize yourself with AIG\u2019s values and culture. AIG emphasizes integrity, teamwork, and innovation. Understanding these values can help you align your behavior and expectations with the company's mission.\n\n2. **Onboarding Process**: Be prepared for an onboarding process that may include orientation sessions, training programs, and introductions to key team members. This is a great opportunity to learn about the company\u2019s policies, procedures, and resources.\n\n3. **Your Role and Responsibilities**: Have a clear understanding of your job description, responsibilities, and expectations. If you have any questions, don\u2019t hesitate to ask your manager or HR for clarification.\n\n4. **Key Policies and Procedures**: Familiarize yourself with AIG\u2019s employee handbook, including policies on workplace conduct, dress code, remote work, time-off requests, and benefits. Knowing these can help you avoid potential pitfalls.\n\n5. **Technology and Tools**: Learn about the technology platforms and tools that AIG uses. This may include email systems, project management software, and communication tools. Make sure you have access to all necessary accounts and understand how to use them.\n\n6. **Networking**: Take the initiative to introduce yourself to your colleagues and team members. Building a professional network within the company can be invaluable for collaboration and support.\n\n7. **Training and Development Opportunities**: AIG often provides training and development resources. Be proactive in seeking out opportunities to enhance your skills and knowledge, whether through formal training programs or informal mentorship.\n\n8. **Performance Expectations**: Understand how your performance will be evaluated. Familiarize yourself with any performance metrics or review processes that will be used to assess your work.\n\n9. **Diversity and Inclusion**: AIG is committed to diversity and inclusion. Engage with initiatives and programs that promote a diverse workplace and be open to learning from colleagues with different backgrounds.\n\n10. **Work-Life Balance**: Recognize the importance of maintaining a healthy work-life balance. Be sure to take breaks, manage your time effectively, and utilize any available wellness resources.\n\n11. **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t be afraid to ask questions if you\u2019re unsure about something. It shows initiative and a willingness to learn. Most colleagues will appreciate your curiosity.\n\n12. **Feedback and Communication**: Be open to receiving feedback and communicate regularly with your supervisor. This will help you understand how you can improve and meet expectations.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, new employees at AIG can better navigate their first day and set themselves up for success in their new roles.",
